Are your parents still alive?

224
00:18:38,246 --> 00:18:42,667
My mom left when I was little. My
dad raised me and he died last year.

225
00:18:43,084 --> 00:18:46,212
Oh, my. So you cared for him as well?

226
00:18:47,755 --> 00:18:49,257
I would have.

227
00:18:49,549 --> 00:18:51,884
I just thought I had more time.

228
00:18:55,013 --> 00:18:56,097
Yeah.

229
00:18:57,098 --> 00:19:00,351
You think too much about the time
you have left...

230
00:19:00,893 --> 00:19:02,937
you don't spend it living.

231
00:19:03,187 --> 00:19:06,274
Be good to my husband.
Be good to his house.

232
00:19:06,941 --> 00:19:08,317
Remedies at 9:00.

233
00:19:08,443 --> 00:19:10,528
One, two, three.

234
00:19:29,964 --> 00:19:33,801
You don't see gardens like this
back in New Jersey, I expect.

235
00:19:35,094 --> 00:19:37,472
Actually, it's the Garden State.

236
00:19:37,972 --> 00:19:40,141
[Laughing] I doubt that very much.

237
00:19:41,726 --> 00:19:44,312
Nothing more glorious than a garden.

238
00:19:44,395 --> 00:19:46,939
Gone every winter, back every spring.

239
00:19:50,443 --> 00:19:52,278
You religious at all?

240
00:19:53,446 --> 00:19:55,573
I try to keep an open mind.

241
00:19:55,907 --> 00:19:57,992
That's good. That's very good.

242
00:19:59,243 --> 00:20:00,995
Where are my trilliums?

243
00:20:01,079 --> 00:20:04,332
Oh, fiddlesticks. Do me a blessing, child.

244
00:20:04,749 --> 00:20:06,668
Will you run up to the attic for me?

245
00:20:06,751 --> 00:20:10,463
